20¤¤Use, storage and disclosure of information
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
When you use your Visa/Dankort card, a record is made of information
including the card number, the transaction sum, the date of use
and the location where your Visa/Dankort card was used. This information
is forwarded to &BANKNAVN. by the business in question.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The information is stored by the business, by the business's bank/Nets
and at &BANKNAVN.. The bank uses this information for bookkeeping, in
account statements and for subsequently correcting any errors.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The information is only otherwise disclosed in cases where this is
required by law or to prevent misuse of the card. The information is
saved for the current year plus five years.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
When registering for Dankort Secure or
Verified by Visa, your mobile phone number will be
stored by Nets and used to send out one-off codes.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
:SWISS10
:FED.
21¤¤Registration of blocked Visa/Dankort card
:SKRSLUT.
.sp 3mm
:SWISS8.
When your Visa/Dankort card has been blocked - see Sections 10 and 12 - it
will be registered in the Danish financial
institutions' shared register of blocked Dankort and
Visa/Dankort cards. Blocked Visa/Dankort numbers will also appear on
any list of blocked cards prepared by Visa.
.sp 3mm
.kp off
.kp on
The shared Dankort register is open to all financial institutions and
businesses that accept payments with Visa/Dankort cards, so that these
banks and businesses can check whether a card that is being used to make
a payment has been blocked.
.sp 5mm
.kp off
.kp on
